Name
job_description:
HR Administrator / Marketing Associate
 
 We are seeking a dedicated HR Administrator/Marketing Associate with over 15 years of experience in customer service and hospitality. The ideal candidate will manage HR functions including recruitment, employee relations, benefits administration, and compliance with labor regulations. This role also involves designing marketing collateral, managing advertising programs, and enhancing our online presence through website management and social media engagement. 
 
 Key responsibilities include resolving employee relations issues, preparing documentation for personnel transactions, and analyzing marketing strategies to improve customer interaction. Strong organizational, communication, and analytical skills are essential, along with a passion for customer satisfaction and team leadership. Certifications in HR and marketing will be an advantage. Join our dynamic team to drive employee engagement and marketing initiatives!

job_description:
HR Specialist, US HR Operations
 
 
 
 We are seeking an HR Specialist to join our US HR Operations team. The ideal candidate will manage communications regarding policy changes and system updates, ensuring seamless information flow. You will design and implement comprehensive training programs for new hires, while auditing job postings and conducting background checks. Additionally, you will facilitate monthly benefits briefings for new employees and serve as a liaison between HR Managers and vendors, addressing any system-related inquiries. Your role will involve providing feedback on process improvements and leading projects such as RFI/RFP initiatives. Proficiency in SharePoint and a strong foundation in HR practices are essential. If you thrive in a dynamic environment and are passionate about enhancing HR operations, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
HR Director
 
 
 
 We are seeking an experienced HR Director with over 20 years in recruiting and 15 years in HR executive management, preferably within a healthcare environment. The ideal candidate will lead recruitment initiatives for clinicians and management teams, develop HR policies, and oversee employee benefits administration. Proficiency in HRIS development and database management is essential, as is the ability to provide coaching to management on performance-related issues. This role involves ensuring compliance with legal requirements, reducing organizational risks, and spearheading innovative HR projects. A Master's degree in Information Management Systems is preferred. Join us to drive HR excellence and enhance employee engagement within our organization.

HR Specialist

The ideal candidate will excel in personnel management and process optimization, ensuring high levels of client satisfaction. Responsibilities include managing inbound email inquiries related to HR policies, resolving client issues, and effectively tracking cases from initiation to resolution using our case management tools. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and strong conflict resolution skills are essential. If you are a motivated team player with a passion for improving customer experiences, we would love to hear from you.

job_description:
HR Manager
 
 We are seeking an experienced HR Manager to lead our Human Resources department. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in HR department startups, employee recruitment and retention, benefits administration, and compliance with employment laws (FMLA, ADA, EEO). You will be responsible for managing employee relations, implementing HR policies and procedures, overseeing performance management, and developing training programs. 
 
 Key responsibilities include fostering a positive workplace culture, ensuring regulatory compliance, and recruiting top talent at all levels. You will also manage HRIS technologies and provide essential reporting to support organizational goals. Strong mediation, negotiation, and conflict resolution skills are essential. The successful candidate will demonstrate strategic thinking, effective communication, and a commitment to continuous improvement. 
 
 Join us to create an inclusive, high-performing environment that enhances employee satisfaction and drives organizational success.

HR Generalist
 
 
 We are seeking a detail-oriented and results-driven HR Generalist to support our human resources operations. The ideal candidate will manage visa-related employment processes for non-immigrant faculty and staff, enhancing productivity and efficiency. Responsibilities include preparing and submitting petitions for USCIS adjudication, maintaining electronic databases, and developing guidelines to comply with USCIS mandates. The HR Generalist will also serve as a liaison for international queries, conduct monthly orientations, and manage the HR website. Strong proficiency in Microsoft Office, exceptional time management skills, and a self-starter attitude are essential. This role offers an opportunity for professional growth and increased responsibility within a dynamic team.

A Bachelor's degree in Sociology or a related field is required, along with a commitment to ongoing professional development in HR best practices. Join our team to foster an inclusive and productive work environment that supports the growth of our staff and faculty.

job_description:
Information Assurance Professional
 
 Job Summary:
 We are seeking a dedicated Information Assurance Professional with extensive experience in enterprise design and engineering. The ideal candidate will excel in analyzing and mitigating risks, ensuring compliance through the Risk Management Framework (RMF), and managing accreditation efforts for departmental modernization projects. Responsibilities include coordinating with stakeholders to achieve successful Authorization To Operate (ATO) decisions, implementing vulnerability management for accredited systems, and supervising external consultants. The role demands proficiency in Active Directory design, data storage engineering, and network troubleshooting. Strong collaboration and decision-making skills are essential for enhancing performance and productivity while maintaining cost-effective solutions.
 
 Key Qualifications:
 - 37 years of experience in IT and enterprise platforms
 - Expertise in PLM, hardware/software upgrades, and project tracking
 - Proficient in Red Hat Enterprise Linux and high-performance computing solutions

job_description:
Information Technology Specialist
 
 Location: [City, State] 
 Job Type: Full-Time 
 
 We are seeking an experienced Information Technology Specialist to manage our IT and communications environment. The ideal candidate will be responsible for planning, coordinating, and installing system designs, hardware, and software to ensure optimal performance across the Wing, Geographically Separated Units (GSUs), and tenant units. You will troubleshoot and diagnose system failures, provide technical support, and implement corrective measures to enhance system reliability. 
 
 Key responsibilities include managing telecommunications networks, analyzing new technologies for compatibility, and maintaining documentation in the Remedy ticketing system. You will also oversee personnel training, evaluate purchase requests, and collaborate with vendors to resolve integration issues. Strong project management skills and the ability to adapt to changing technologies are essential for success in this role. 
 
 Join us in fostering a reliable and efficient IT environment that supports our mission requirements.

Manage the assigned IT/communications environment with privileged access at the network level for the Wing, Geographically Separated Units (GSU), and Tenants.  Plan, coordinate, install, and continuously analyze system design, hardware and software. Continually plan, install, and analyze new hardware, software and processes to ensure networks are reliable and efficient.  Serve as a focal point for ensuring functionality and operability of the assigned IT/data systems/functions, voice, and wireless systems to support mission requirements.  Optimize, analyze, manage, and direct installation of any new hardware or software introduced into the environment to ensure its compatibility with existing architecture, its reliability, and functionality in relation to the organization's business requirements.  Oversee and initiate corrective or preventative measures to rectify immediate problems and prevent future occurrences through the CFP.  Troubleshoot and diagnose system failures to isolate source of problems.  Provide customer technical assistance/support for all users.  Provide management with information necessary to address difficult/complex problems.  Review purchase requests, SOW's ensuring documentation is sufficient to justify enhancements to keep systems current. job_description:
Information Technology Instructor
 
 We are seeking an experienced Information Technology Instructor to join our team. The ideal candidate will possess over 17 years in the IT field, with a strong background in curriculum design and computer-based training development. Responsibilities include managing student learning needs, creating and updating IT program curriculum, and overseeing part-time instructors. You will teach multiple classes and utilize data analysis to assess student progress while maintaining accreditation standards. A focus on student counseling and tailored customer service training for IT students is essential. The candidate should demonstrate excellent problem-solving abilities, project management skills, and experience in team building. A Master's degree in Learning & Technology or related field is preferred, along with proficiency in various multimedia design tools and IT software. Join us to inspire the next generation of IT professionals!

job_description:
Information Technology Auditor
 
 
 
 We are seeking an experienced Information Technology Auditor to join our team. In this role, you will conduct comprehensive IT audits, focusing on user access, database configurations, and compliance with security policies. You will participate in annual risk assessments and assist with Sarbanes Oxley (SOX) compliance, including control testing and remediation efforts. Your expertise in PeopleSoft (HCM and Financials), SQL, and various auditing tools will be crucial as you collaborate with IT and external auditors. Additionally, you will provide guidance on IT upgrades and contribute to training initiatives for internal audit staff. Strong analytical skills and knowledge of regulatory standards (CIP, WECC, FERC, NERC, MRO) are essential. Join us to enhance our audit processes and ensure robust IT governance.

job_description:
Director of Information Technology
 
 We are seeking an experienced Director of Information Technology to lead our IT operations and strategy. The ideal candidate will oversee a team responsible for managing a robust network infrastructure supporting over 200 users. Key responsibilities include implementing cost-effective IT solutions, managing vendor relationships, and ensuring compliance with PCI security standards. The Director will spearhead the design and deployment of networking and communication systems, including MPLS and VoIP technologies, while optimizing IT budgets. This role requires strong expertise in Cisco networking hardware, Windows and Linux operating systems, and IT governance practices. The successful candidate will foster a collaborative environment, providing strategic insights and reporting to executive leadership. A CISCO Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification is preferred. Join us in driving technological innovation and enhancing operational efficiency.

job_description:
Director of Information Technology
 
 We are seeking an experienced Director of Information Technology to lead our IT operations and strategy. The ideal candidate will oversee a team responsible for managing a robust network infrastructure supporting over 200 users. Key responsibilities include implementing cost-effective IT solutions, managing vendor relationships, and ensuring compliance with PCI security standards. The Director will spearhead the design and deployment of networking and communication systems, including MPLS and VoIP technologies, while optimizing IT budgets. This role requires strong expertise in Cisco networking hardware, Windows and Linux operating systems, and IT governance practices. The successful candidate will foster a collaborative environment, providing strategic insights and reporting to executive leadership. A CISCO Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification is preferred. Join us in driving technological innovation and enhancing operational efficiency.

job_description:
Director of Information Technology
 
 We are seeking an experienced Director of Information Technology to lead our IT operations and strategy. The ideal candidate will oversee a team responsible for managing a robust network infrastructure supporting over 200 users. Key responsibilities include implementing cost-effective IT solutions, managing vendor relationships, and ensuring compliance with PCI security standards. The Director will spearhead the design and deployment of networking and communication systems, including MPLS and VoIP technologies, while optimizing IT budgets. This role requires strong expertise in Cisco networking hardware, Windows and Linux operating systems, and IT governance practices. The successful candidate will foster a collaborative environment, providing strategic insights and reporting to executive leadership. A CISCO Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification is preferred. Join us in driving technological innovation and enhancing operational efficiency.

job_description:
Information Technology Provisioning Technician
 
 
 
 We are seeking a detail-oriented Information Technology Provisioning Technician to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have 5 years of experience in IT and security, with a proven track record in managing enterprise security initiatives. You will be responsible for provisioning, troubleshooting, and repairing laptops, desktops, and mobile devices while providing tier 2 and 3 support to a diverse user base. Your role will involve Active Directory administration, including SSO integration and user management, as well as collaborating cross-functionally to enhance business processes and optimize technology investments. Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to mentor junior staff are essential. Familiarity with security compliance, risk management, and IT governance will be key to ensuring effective business protection and continuity. If you are a self-motivated leader with a passion for technology and security, we want to hear from you!

Information Technology Provisioning Technician
 
 
 
 We are seeking a detail-oriented Information Technology Provisioning Technician to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have 5 years of experience in IT and security, with a proven track record in managing enterprise security initiatives. You will be responsible for provisioning, troubleshooting, and repairing laptops, desktops, and mobile devices while providing tier 2 and 3 support to a diverse user base. Your role will involve Active Directory administration, including SSO integration and user management, as well as collaborating cross-functionally to enhance business processes and optimize technology investments. Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to mentor junior staff are essential. Familiarity with security compliance, risk management, and IT governance will be key to ensuring effective business protection and continuity. If you are a self-motivated leader with a passion for technology and security, we want to hear from you!

 Overview:
 We are seeking an experienced IT Specialist to manage and implement complex data networks and telecommunications systems for the U.S. Army Information Systems Engineering Command. The ideal candidate will lead projects related to local area networks (LANs) and visual information systems, ensuring the infrastructure meets technical specifications and security standards.

 Qualifications:

Information Technology (IT) Specialist
 
 Location: Fort Huachuca, AZ
 
 Overview:
 We are seeking an experienced IT Specialist to manage and implement complex data networks and telecommunications systems for the U.S. Army Information Systems Engineering Command. The ideal candidate will lead projects related to local area networks (LANs) and visual information systems, ensuring the infrastructure meets technical specifications and security standards.
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Direct and manage project teams to deliver IT infrastructure solutions, including a $25 million C4 facility for Joint Special Operations Command.
 - Develop system design plans, technical requirements, and oversee construction documentation.
 - Coordinate with stakeholders to resolve project issues and ensure compliance with user requirements.
 - Create integrated master schedules (IMS) for resource management, tracking project deliverables and performance.
 
 Qualifications:
 - Bachelor‚Äôs Degree in Information Technology or related field.
 - Proven experience in IT project management and systems integration.

input_text:
Optional demographic disclosure: Race: Asian; Nationality: American.

Luna Jackson          INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT) SPECIALIST                 Experience      Information Technology (IT) Specialist      January 2012     Company Name                IT Specialist Project Engineer    December 2009   to   Current       City  ,   State      U.S.  Army Information Systems Engineering Command (USAISEC) on projects involving large and complex data networks and telecommunications systems while assigned to the Fort Huachuca Engineering Directorate of USAISEC.  I develop, manage and coordinate the implementation of network communications, local area networks (LANs), visual information systems (VIS), and information technology (IT) infrastructure  projects.  As the Project Manager and Lead Engineer, I directed and managed the efforts of a five person Integrated Product Team (IPT)  to implement the $25 million IT infrastructure for the the new Command, Control, Communications and Computers (C4) facility for the Joint Special Operations Command (JSOC) at Ft Bragg, NC.  Provided daily project coordination and oversaw the development of the IT technical requirements, system design plan and associated contract documents and design drawings  for the 35,000 sf building.  Reviewed building construction design drawings, consolidated design change input requests from the customer and team members, and provided justification for the proposed design changes and building modifications to ensure that the IT infrastructure was installed according to technical specifications, applicable security standards,  and customer requirements.  requests for building design changes to the US Army Corps of Engineers (USACE).  and provided technical oversight of the project.  Represented JSOC and ISEC in project meetings with the USACE and other project stakeholders for technical requirements, project scheduling updates, and to resolve controversial project issues.  Created the project integrated master schedule (IMS) to identify and manage resources so that all project documentation and deliverables were developed accurately, and to ensure system reliability, operability, and maintainability.  In support of the Army Base Realignment and Closure (BRAC) process, performed duties as the project coordinator for the $19 million BRAC mandated Army Central Command (ARCENT) Headquarters relocation.  As the ARCENT relocation project leader, identified and analyzed requirements, assigned and reviewed work and exercised full control over the planning, development, and implementation of all assigned tasks for the Integrated Product Team (IPT).  Obtained contract engineering services by developing the Acquisition Requirements Package (ARP), and participated in Source Selection Evaluation Board (SSEB) activities.  Prepared statements of work (SOWs), procurement data packages, and evaluated contractor work performance and provided the monthly performance report to the contracting office and weekly project status updates to ISEC management.  Provided financial and resource planning, execution, and tracking; to include manpower, temporary duty (TDY), and other acquisition resource requirements.  Judiciously expended project resources, determined priorities and worked within resource allocation limits, fiscal law and existing policy.  Completed all required contract modifications, List of Materials (LOMs) and Major Item List of Materials (MILOMs), as well as independent government cost estimates (IGCEs) as required.  Integrated various IT sub-systems based on system dependencies, technical adequacies, and customers' need.  Conducted technical reviews of proposed test plans and monitored the System Acceptance Testing (SAT) of all IT and VIS systems and proposed solutions to faults identified in the SAT to ensure continuity of new and existing systems and compliance with user requirements.          Systems Integration Analyst    July 2009   to   December 2009     Company Name   －   City  ,   State      Supervisor:  Randy Devine - (520) 459-3174.  Systems Integration Analyst responsible for contract Information Technology (IT) engineering services in support of the US Army Information Systems Engineering Command (USAISEC).  Developed the Facility Design Criteria (FDC), System Design Plans (SDPs), Engineering Installation Packages (EIPs), List of Materials (LOMs) and other acquisition documentation for complex IT projects according to user requirements.  Worked with Government and sub-contractor personnel and provided guidance and oversight on project document development and validation for the U.S.  Army Forces Command (FORSCOM) and U.S.  Army Reserve Command (USARC) BRAC relocation.  Provided engineering, procurement, installation, cutover and testing requirements for the High Frequency (HF) and Ultra High Frequency (UHF) Radio Systems and antennas in support of a Command, Control, Communications, Computers and Intelligence / Information Technology (C4I/IT) systems project.  Reviewed project documentation and ensured contract deliverables were complete and delivered accurately and on time as specified in the Acquisition Requirements Package (ARP).             April 2001   to   September 2009     Company Name          Functional Area Expert (Command and Control)Sierra Vista, Arizona Supervisor: Robert Kessler - (520) 417-0959.  Communications Engineer supporting the U.S.  Army Information Systems Engineering Command (USAISEC) by providing IT engineering services in the form of quick reaction engineering to Engineer, Furnish, Install, and Test (EFIT) total communications functionality at multiple Command and Control (C2) facilities.  Provided QA / QC checks and Acceptance Testing on various projects involving C2 facility upgrades as well as Command Headquarters relocations.  Provided IT engineering support for the US Southern Command (SOUTHCOM) headquarters relocation project, to include developing the FDC as part of the design-build contracting process for the USACE.  Developed the SDP, LOM, cost estimates and test plans for the radio and satellite systems, copper and fiber cable plant, lightning protection systems, grounding, bonding and shielding systems and related infrastructure for the Defense Threat Reduction Agency (DTRA) relocation project.  Provided on-site engineering support for the voice, data, and visual information systems being installed for the United States Army South (USARSO) Headquarters and the Installation Management Agency (IMA) at Fort Sam Houston, Texas.  Provided detailed engineering for the design and installation of Briefing and Display Facilities (BDF), Conference Rooms, Command Center Areas, Telecommunications Rooms (TRs), and Open Office Areas.  Conducted QA / QC checks and testing for a Defense Red Switch Network (DRSN), Global Command and Control System (GCCS), Unclassified Local Area Network (NIPRNET), Secret Local Area Network (SIPRNET), Sensitive Compartmented Local Area Network (SCI LAN), Administrative Telephone System, and Visual Information Systems.  Assisted USAISEC Force Projection Engineering Directorate, and 1st Signal Brigade personnel in the design and installation of a C2 facility upgrade at the 19th Theatre Support Command in South Korea.  Performed site surveys, gathered user requirements from several staff directorates and operational elements within the command and developed an SDP, EIP and LOMs to upgrade the Global Command and Control System (GCCS) communications systems as well as the administrative and tactical voice systems.  Provided engineering support for the development of the C2 facility for the U.S.  Army Central Command (USCENTCOM) Headquarters and foreign coalition forces in Doha, Qatar in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom.  These efforts included various secure voice, data, and visual information systems critical to the Command Center operations.  Supervised and assisted with the routing, termination and acceptance testing of all fiber optic and Cat5 cabling, voice and data systems and related telecommunications equipment and infrastructure.  We are seeking a dedicated and motivated Adjunct Science Teacher to join our educational team. The successful applicant will demonstrate strong communication skills and a commitment to enhancing student literacy in science. 
 
 Join us in inspiring the next generation of scientists!

job_description:
Special Education Teacher
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Special Education Teacher with a strong background in supporting students with Autism and behavioral disorders. The ideal candidate will have at least 10 years of experience in creating engaging lesson plans tailored to diverse learning styles and managing Individualized Education Programs (IEPs). This role involves collaborating with a multidisciplinary team, including specialists and classroom teachers, to promote academic and social-emotional growth. 
 
 Key responsibilities include providing crisis intervention, adapting teaching strategies, and fostering a positive learning environment. The candidate should possess an Arizona Teaching Certificate with a Special Education endorsement and demonstrate exceptional communication skills. Experience in managing teams and coordinating educational services is essential. A commitment to data-driven goal setting and continuous professional development is required to ensure student success. Join us in making a meaningful impact in the lives of our students!

job_description:
Special Education Teacher
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Special Education Teacher with a strong background in supporting students with Autism and behavioral disorders. The ideal candidate will have at least 10 years of experience in creating engaging lesson plans tailored to diverse learning styles and managing Individualized Education Programs (IEPs). This role involves collaborating with a multidisciplinary team, including specialists and classroom teachers, to promote academic and social-emotional growth. 
 
 Key responsibilities include providing crisis intervention, adapting teaching strategies, and fostering a positive learning environment. The candidate should possess an Arizona Teaching Certificate with a Special Education endorsement and demonstrate exceptional communication skills. Experience in managing teams and coordinating educational services is essential. A commitment to data-driven goal setting and continuous professional development is required to ensure student success. Join us in making a meaningful impact in the lives of our students!

job_description:
Director of Special Education
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Director of Special Education to lead our initiatives in supporting students with exceptionalities, particularly those with visual impairments. The ideal candidate will possess strong leadership skills, with a proven track record in special education laws, compliance, and instructional coaching. This role involves collaborating with educators, parents, and community organizations to develop tailored educational programs and ensure adherence to IDEA guidelines.
 
 Key responsibilities include overseeing IEP implementation, facilitating professional development for staff, and promoting inclusive practices within the school. The Director will also analyze data to drive instructional improvements and enhance student outcomes. A commitment to advocacy and enhancing the lives of underserved communities is essential. The successful candidate will hold a Master's degree in Administration and Supervision, along with relevant certifications in special education. Join us in fostering an environment where all students can thrive.

job_description:
Elementary School Teacher (Grades 1-5)
 
 We are seeking a dedicated and innovative Elementary School Teacher to join our team. The ideal candidate will possess a Level 2 Teaching Certification and have a strong background in fostering a supportive and inclusive classroom environment. Responsibilities include developing and implementing engaging lesson plans, utilizing diverse instructional strategies to meet the needs of all students, and assessing student progress through various evaluation methods. The teacher will also ensure effective communication with parents and collaborate with colleagues to enhance curriculum development. A passion for teaching and a commitment to the academic success of culturally diverse students is essential. If you have a proven track record of creating stimulating learning experiences that prepare students for a competitive future, we encourage you to apply.

Certification (K-5), makes me a worthy contender for a teacher position at your school .Utilizing my skills and expertise, I am eager to become a key member of your team.

* Well versed in assisting children in build social, cognitive, emotional, and physical skills. * Adept at providing a stimulating conducive classroom environment. * Special talent for utilizing the highest quality teaching resources and classroom materials.
It is paramount that in order to become the best teacher, good interaction with the students is essential - aside from imparting good knowledge. The expectation of what the students think and how they would think in a particular state of affairs is equally important in my point of view.
In addition, I apply an innovative teaching approach which includes the incorporation of 21st century skill sets that will prepare my students to compete with other students both nationally and internationally. 
Of all my strengths, I take extreme pride in the patience and dedication required to meet the needs of children from socially and culturally diverse backgrounds. My insight not only comes from my years in the classroom as a teacher, but also from my years a pupil. Having lived abroad for many of my formative years, as well as some after college, I understand the delicate balance that is needed to make learning inclusive to all. job_description:
Director of Business Development
 
 Job Summary: 
 We are seeking a dynamic Director of Business Development to drive revenue growth and market expansion. The ideal candidate will leverage strategic leadership and innovative sales techniques to enhance business practices and client engagement. Responsibilities include developing and executing tactical plans to secure new business opportunities, managing client relationships, and overseeing account management. The role requires collaboration with executive leadership to devise strategies that maximize profit margins and brand recognition. You will lead a team, implement operational improvements, and build strong vendor partnerships. A proven track record in sales leadership, market analysis, and process improvement is essential.
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Develop and execute business development strategies 
 - Manage and expand client relationships 
 - Lead sales forecasting and presentations 
 - Drive operational improvements and cost reduction initiatives 
 - Oversee logistics for large-scale events and transportation services 
 
 Qualifications: 
 - Strong background in sales and business development 
 - Excellent leadership and team-building skills 
 - Experience in strategic planning and market analysis

Olivia Flores          HEALTHCARE           Executive Profile    Cynthia was also an instructor for the Cap Gemini Ernst & Young Global Regulatory Compliance Boot Camp where members of the CGE&Y Regulatory Compliance Team are immersed in global regulatory compliance, Good Manufacturing Practices, Good Clinical Practices, Good Laboratory Practices, CGE&Y validation tools and methodology.  Working with the international workforce of CGE&Y, Cynthia was required to be flexible, sensitive and creative in her methods of teaching   
Cynthia's nursing career focus was in Pain Management, Emergency Nursing, Legal Nurse Consulting and Life Care Planning. She has traveled extensively throughout the U. S. and worldwide as a Health Care and Life Sciences Consultant for G Major Consulting, Cap Gemini Ernst & Young, Accenture, and Ness Technologies. 
While working in clinical nursing, Cynthia worked in acute, home care and long term care arenas. As a Case Manager and Life Care Planner Cynthia was an adjunct instructor for the University of Florida Rehabilitation Training Institute and authored and taught Life Care Planning and Aging in the Catastrophically Injured. As a Project manager for several Global Regulatory Compliance/Life Sciences teams, Glidewell has a strong background in communication skills.  Her ability to work with people from various ethnic, cultural, and educational backgrounds has been key in her success as a Regulatory Compliance/ Validation Systems manager.  She has frequently been instrumental in the establishment and training of off shore call center personnel for specific projects in  IT support situations.  Her experience has given her in depth insight to the cultural nuances of different populations ranging from India to the elderly.  Her writing background includes authoring a Life Care Planning in the Catastrophically Injured Aging for the University of Florida Rehabilitation Training Institute, Adverse Events Reporting for RN's for Abbott Laboratories, and numerous other educational materials for diverse audiences. job_description:
Healthcare Administrator
 
 We are seeking a skilled Healthcare Administrator to oversee the daily operations of our healthcare facility. The ideal candidate will demonstrate strong leadership and communication abilities, managing multiple administrative tasks while ensuring compliance with healthcare regulations. Responsibilities include supervising department operations, coordinating budgetary adherence with finance, processing performance reports, and ensuring the accuracy of medical records. The administrator will also revise policies in line with changing laws, facilitate new employee orientations, and act as a liaison between management and staff. A commitment to patient-focused care and continuous process improvement is essential. Candidates should possess a strong background in healthcare informatics, business operations, and relationship management. An MBA in Health Services Administration or related field is preferred. Join our team to make a positive impact in healthcare administration.

job_description:
Healthcare Consultant
 
 We are seeking a dynamic Healthcare Consultant with a proven track record in leadership, training, and healthcare program development. The ideal candidate will leverage extensive military experience and expertise in medical education to mentor new healthcare specialists and lead training initiatives for diverse audiences. Responsibilities include designing and delivering curriculum for EMT and advanced medical training, managing logistics for key healthcare events, and providing tailored lifestyle and treatment planning for clients in a high-stakes environment. Proficiency in project management and public speaking is essential, along with strong skills in Microsoft Office and healthcare technology. This role demands a compassionate leader capable of guiding individuals through complex medical processes while fostering a culture of excellence. Join us to make a significant impact in the healthcare sector!

job_description:
Healthcare Associate
 
 We are seeking an energetic and resourceful Healthcare Associate to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will demonstrate strong leadership and communication skills while supporting day-to-day operations in a fast-paced environment. Responsibilities include managing patient scheduling and discharge processes, coordinating admission packages, arranging transportation, and maintaining accurate medical records. 
 
 The successful candidate will utilize EPIC and Microsoft Office Suite to maintain databases and generate reports, ensuring adherence to quality standards and deadlines. Strong organizational and multitasking abilities are essential, along with a commitment to exceptional patient service. This role requires effective collaboration with diverse teams and a proactive approach to problem-solving. 
 
 Join us in delivering outstanding healthcare service while contributing to a productive and efficient work environment.

job_description:
Healthcare Consultant
 
 
 We are seeking a dynamic Healthcare Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their extensive experience in network development and provider engagement to establish a Medicare Advantage I-SNP in the northeast. This role involves identifying and contracting with healthcare providers to meet CMS time/distance standards, while serving as a subject matter expert on best practices. The successful candidate will possess strong analytical skills, a dedication to improving healthcare quality, and the ability to build lasting relationships with providers. Proven experience in leading teams, conducting market analyses, and enhancing operational performance is essential. If you are motivated, responsible, and passionate about healthcare improvement, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
Healthcare Consultant
 
 
 We are seeking a dynamic Healthcare Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their extensive experience in network development and provider engagement to establish a Medicare Advantage I-SNP in the northeast. This role involves identifying and contracting with healthcare providers to meet CMS time/distance standards, while serving as a subject matter expert on best practices. The successful candidate will possess strong analytical skills, a dedication to improving healthcare quality, and the ability to build lasting relationships with providers. Proven experience in leading teams, conducting market analyses, and enhancing operational performance is essential. If you are motivated, responsible, and passionate about healthcare improvement, we encourage you to apply.

 - Strong leadership skills with the ability to work collaboratively across diverse teams.

job_description:
Healthcare Recruiter
 
 
 
 We are seeking a motivated and customer-focused Healthcare Recruiter to join our dynamic clinical staffing firm. The ideal candidate will possess exceptional interpersonal skills and a strong background in human resources and administrative support. In this role, you will consult with HR professionals across various healthcare facilities to assess staffing needs and develop strategic partnerships. You will manage the full recruitment lifecycle, including candidate screening, interviewing, and onboarding. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and data management is essential, along with the ability to analyze client requirements and implement effective marketing strategies. job_description:
Agriculture Advisor and Language Officer
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Agriculture Advisor and Language Officer to enhance agricultural development initiatives in Afghanistan. The ideal candidate will possess a strong background in agriculture, with a Bachelor's degree from Nangarhar Agriculture Faculty, and experience in coordinating with governmental and non-governmental organizations. Responsibilities include facilitating communication between local authorities, participating in provincial development meetings, and conducting training workshops for students and community members on agricultural practices and business development. Proficiency in English, Pashto, and Dari is essential for translating documents and providing simultaneous interpretation during meetings. The candidate will also support project planning and implementation, assess training needs, and develop educational materials for various stakeholders. A commitment to community engagement and capacity building is vital to ensure sustainable agricultural practices and improved living standards.

job_description:
Agriculture Advisor and Language Officer
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Agriculture Advisor and Language Officer to enhance agricultural development initiatives in Afghanistan. The ideal candidate will possess a strong background in agriculture, with a Bachelor's degree from Nangarhar Agriculture Faculty, and experience in coordinating with governmental and non-governmental organizations. Responsibilities include facilitating communication between local authorities, participating in provincial development meetings, and conducting training workshops for students and community members on agricultural practices and business development. Proficiency in English, Pashto, and Dari is essential for translating documents and providing simultaneous interpretation during meetings. The candidate will also support project planning and implementation, assess training needs, and develop educational materials for various stakeholders. A commitment to community engagement and capacity building is vital to ensure sustainable agricultural practices and improved living standards.

job_description:
Program Support Assistant
 
 We are seeking a detail-oriented Program Support Assistant to enhance our operations within a veteran support program. The ideal candidate will be responsible for managing claims matching, processing refunds, and conducting thorough account audits for veteran accounts. You will prepare public vouchers, assist with Debt Management and Treasury Offset Programs, and ensure accurate data collection and analysis. 
 
 Key responsibilities include:
 - Producing voucher refunds and processing returned checks.
 - Reviewing claims and determining insurance payment applications.
 - Providing clerical and technical support to operations.
 - Compiling and tracking data for financial and administrative reports.
 - Preparing written correspondence and assisting in audit requests.
 
 Candidates should possess strong analytical skills, experience with automated systems, and a commitment to supporting our veteran community. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and familiarity with data analysis tools is preferred.

job_description:
E-Commerce Supervisor
 
 We are seeking a dedicated E-Commerce Supervisor to oversee daily operations and enhance productivity within our team. The ideal candidate will excel in strategic planning and possess strong organizational skills to manage workloads efficiently. You will lead, train, and develop employees while fostering a culture of teamwork and continuous improvement aligned with company values. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and experience with warehouse management systems (Exeter WMS) will be essential. The successful candidate will be a quick learner, safety-conscious, and possess excellent multitasking abilities. Join us to drive performance and achieve our business objectives!

job_description:
E-Commerce Supervisor
 
 We are seeking a dedicated E-Commerce Supervisor to oversee daily operations and enhance productivity within our team. The ideal candidate will excel in strategic planning and possess strong organizational skills to manage workloads efficiently. You will lead, train, and develop employees while fostering a culture of teamwork and continuous improvement aligned with company values. Your role will involve identifying safety and quality enhancement opportunities and communicating these initiatives across the organization. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and experience with warehouse management systems (Exeter WMS) will be essential. The successful candidate will be a quick learner, safety-conscious, and possess excellent multitasking abilities. Join us to drive performance and achieve our business objectives!

job_description:
Project Assistant
 
 Job Overview:
 We are seeking a motivated Project Assistant to support our Rural Agriculture Revitalisation Programme. The ideal candidate will be flexible, detail-oriented, and possess strong communication skills to facilitate project tasks effectively.
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Assist in project monitoring, evaluation, and timely reporting of results.
 - Support documentation and knowledge sharing among stakeholders.
 - Coordinate training workshops and stakeholder field visits.
 - Help draft proposals and maintain accurate project records.
 - Contribute to the development of monitoring and evaluation tools.
 
 Qualifications:
 - Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Development Studies or related field.
 - Proficient in statistical packages and report writing.
 - Strong administrative skills with a service-oriented approach.
 - Experience in project management and agricultural development is a plus.
 
 Join us to make a positive impact in the agricultural sector while developing your skills in a supportive team environment.

This $6 million Danida funded program which is coming to an end on 31 December 2015 has the following components ;value chain development (oil seeds, horticulture and dairy), value chain financing, matching grant facility for SMEs, e-Extension, agro-dealer development and Pilots and Studies.  Some of my responsibilities include: Monitoring and Evaluation Assisting in project monitoring evaluation and timeous reporting on the same as required Assisting in the contribution of feedback processes, coaching and evaluation of achieved results for client and SNV Assisting  in proposing corrective measures and lessons learnt based on evaluations Knowledge development and communication Implementing the process of documentation and knowledge development in the project and facilitate sharing with stakeholders Developed a concept note of fisheries Assisting in ensuring that lessons learned are shared and applied in daily practice Ensuring submission of quality reports by Local Capacity Builders Support to project administration Assisting in facilitation of training workshops and report writing Coordinating stakeholder field visits Keeping agenda up to date, arranging meetings and appointments Assisting in the drafting of proposals Assisting in the Company                Netherlands Development Organisation (SNV).          Agriculture Sector Intern   06/2014   to   08/2014     Company Name   City  ,   State       3 months contract assisting a FAO Funded Project that was aimed at sustaining and improving the livelihoods of vulnerable and emerging rural farming households in Zimbabwe and thus reduce their dependency on humanitarian assistance.  The project was meant to build capacity of farmer groups so that they provide essential production, marketing and business development services to their members.          Attache   05/2013   to   02/2014     Company Name   City  ,   State       I was an attaché under the RARP- CSF programme in the Agriculture sector from May 2013 to February 2014.  During the time I was attached I provided both administrative and programme support and back up assistance for the sector specifically RARP- CSF.  Whilst working with the Agriculture sector, I acquired an understanding of development work and my duties included: Strengthening the documentation process and the process of data collection, data entry analysis as well as contributing towards the development of case studies and related articles for publication Supporting the development of a data management system to ensure safe and efficient upkeep of RARP programme documents Payments compliance and processing Assisting with regular field visits for data collection and analysis Assist with coordination of stakeholder field visits Preparing requests for funds to support project activities.  Maintaining inventory of project assets/resources Organizing venues and invitations to project meetings - making travel arrangements Taking minutes during meetings or key events for dissemination Participating in the development and application of monitoring and evaluation tools and reporting systems.  Sharing of project reports and activity plans with key stakeholders. job_description:
Adult Education Instructor
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Adult Education Instructor with over 20 years of experience in agricultural education and credit recovery programs. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record of fostering student success through innovative lesson planning and community engagement. Responsibilities include developing a comprehensive diploma program tailored to community needs, creating interactive learning mediums, and implementing effective classroom management strategies. The instructor will also facilitate communication with parents, provide student-centered curriculum planning, and support students in achieving academic and vocational goals. A compassionate approach and strong leadership skills are essential for this role. Join us in empowering adult learners to reach their full potential!

 We are seeking a dedicated Adult Education Instructor with over 20 years of experience in agricultural education and credit recovery programs. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record of fostering student success through innovative lesson planning and community engagement. Responsibilities include developing a comprehensive diploma program tailored to community needs, creating interactive learning mediums, and implementing effective classroom management strategies. A compassionate approach and strong leadership skills are essential for this role. Join us in empowering adult learners to reach their full potential!

job_description:
Community Development and Environmental Support Specialist
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Community Development and Environmental Support Specialist with a passion for sustainable practices. The ideal candidate will bring 5 years of outdoor and forestry experience, including hands-on project planning and implementation. Responsibilities include creating and managing data reports, providing logistical support for community health initiatives, and promoting environmental restoration projects. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in retail sales, with experience in upselling and cross-selling services to enhance customer satisfaction. You will be responsible for driving new business acquisition while effectively retaining existing clients by understanding their needs and recommending suitable products. 
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Meet monthly sales quotas through add-on and upsell strategies.
 - Provide exceptional customer service in a fast-paced environment.
 - Conduct cold calls and generate leads for new business opportunities.
 - Assist customers in selecting the best plans and products for their requirements.
 
 Qualifications:
 - Strong client relations and communication skills.
 - Experience in retail or insurance sales is a plus.
 - Ability to thrive in a results-driven environment. 
 
 Join us and contribute to our success while advancing your career!

Sales and Operations Manager
 
 Location: [City, State]
 
 Job Summary:
 We are seeking an experienced Sales and Operations Manager with over 17 years in retail and automotive sales. The ideal candidate will excel in hiring, training, and coaching teams to drive sales and operational success. You will oversee multiple locations, develop and implement effective sales strategies, and enhance employee engagement. Your strong negotiation skills and detail-oriented approach will contribute to achieving organizational goals.
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Lead and mentor sales teams to achieve performance metrics and improve customer satisfaction.
 - Develop and execute sales and merchandising policies adopted company-wide.
 - Manage day-to-day operations, including P&L oversight and inventory control.
 - Conduct training and onboarding programs to enhance staff capabilities.
 - Foster a high-performance culture through effective communication and conflict resolution.
 
 Qualifications:
 - Proven sales leadership with a track record of exceeding targets.
 - Strong interpersonal and coaching skills.
 - Experience in operations and human resource management.

 We are seeking an experienced IT Sales Consultant with a proven track record in driving technology solutions that enhance business efficiency. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience in implementing enterprise systems and leading user training initiatives, particularly in the transition to paperless environments. This role involves identifying client needs, developing tailored proposals, and facilitating stakeholder engagement to ensure successful project outcomes.
 
 The consultant will leverage strong analytical and problem-solving skills to address complex business challenges and improve operational workflows. Excellent communication abilities are essential, as you will be responsible for presenting solutions to diverse audiences and fostering strong relationships with clients. A background in project management practices and technical writing is preferred. Travel may be required to provide hands-on training and support.
 
 Join us to help businesses transform through innovative technology solutions!

 We are seeking a motivated Sales and Customer Service Associate with over 5 years of retail experience in a dynamic, team-oriented environment. The ideal candidate will excel in delivering exceptional customer support, resolving complaints, and fostering strong client relationships. Responsibilities include accurately describing products, managing cash transactions, and effectively communicating with vendors and team members. As a trusted key holder, you will be responsible for opening and closing the store, ensuring a welcoming atmosphere for customers. Proficiency in MS Windows, bilingual communication in English and Spanish, and a knack for creative problem-solving are essential. Join us to leverage your skills and contribute to a goal-oriented team dedicated to providing outstanding service and driving sales success. Flexible scheduling and a calm demeanor under pressure are a must.

job_description:
Culinary Professional with Healthcare Experience
 
 We are seeking a dedicated Culinary Professional with a strong foundation in both the food industry and healthcare settings. The ideal candidate will possess a degree in Culinary Arts and experience as a Private Chef, showcasing exceptional cooking skills and attention to detail. Additionally, prior experience as a Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) will provide invaluable insight into dietary needs and patient care.
 
 Key responsibilities include preparing nutritious meals, ensuring dietary restrictions are met, and maintaining a clean kitchen environment. The candidate must demonstrate strong multitasking abilities, compassionate patient interaction, and effective communication skills. Familiarity with medical terminology and basic healthcare procedures is a plus.
 
 If you are passionate about combining culinary excellence with patient care, we invite you to apply and join our team in making a meaningful impact on the lives of those we serve.

job_description:
Fast Food Chef / Warehouse Picker
 
 
 
 We are seeking an enthusiastic and dedicated Fast Food Chef with experience in food preparation, customer service, and cash handling. The ideal candidate will efficiently prepare and serve high-quality meals while ensuring a friendly and welcoming environment for our customers. Responsibilities include operating kitchen equipment, maintaining cleanliness and safety standards, and mastering the POS system for accurate order processing.
 
 Additionally, candidates with warehouse experience are encouraged to apply. As a Warehouse Picker, you will manage material handling, stock inventory, and assist with shipping and receiving operations. You will contribute to process improvements and ensure accurate record-keeping.
 
 Key skills include strong interpersonal communication, adaptability, and a commitment to safety and efficiency. Join our team and help us deliver exceptional food and service to our valued customers!

 - Strong communication skills and a passion for culinary excellence. 
 
 Join us to create memorable dining experiences!

 If you are a team player with a passion for culinary arts and a commitment to maintaining a safe and efficient kitchen environment, we would love to have you join our team.

 - Monitor food inventory and assist with purchasing.
 - Provide excellent customer service and address guest inquiries promptly.
 
 Qualifications:
 - ServSafe certification preferred.
 - Strong communication and teamwork skills.

job_description:
Line Cook
 
 Job Summary: 
 We are seeking a dedicated Line Cook to join our dynamic kitchen team. The ideal candidate will have a strong focus on quality and efficiency, capable of preparing and plating a wide variety of dishes in a fast-paced, high-volume environment. With at least 2 years of experience, you will be responsible for managing food prep, ensuring adherence to safety and sanitation standards, and maintaining a clean workspace. Your culinary skills will contribute to menu innovation and exceptional guest experiences while effectively controlling portion sizes and food costs. Bilingual candidates (English/Spanish) are encouraged to apply.
 
 Responsibilities:
 - Prepare and cook high-quality dishes according to recipes.
 - Maintain a clean and organized kitchen environment.
 - Collaborate with kitchen staff to ensure smooth operations.
 - Monitor food inventory and assist with purchasing.
 - Provide excellent customer service and address guest inquiries promptly.
 
 Qualifications:
 - ServSafe certification preferred.
 - Strong communication and teamwork skills.

job_description:
Chef
 
 
 
 We are seeking a passionate and experienced Chef to lead our culinary team in a dynamic hospital kitchen environment. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in menu development, staff management, and food safety compliance. Responsibilities include overseeing all kitchen operations, managing staffing and payroll, ensuring adherence to specialized dietary needs, and maintaining food quality and presentation standards. 
 
 The Chef will collaborate closely with dietetic technicians and dietitians to create flavorful and nutritious recipes, monitor food and labor costs to optimize budgets, and implement effective training programs for kitchen staff. Exceptional communication skills and a commitment to customer service are essential, as well as the ability to resolve guest concerns promptly. Join us to enhance our culinary offerings while fostering a collaborative and productive kitchen atmosphere.

job_description:
Chef
 
 
 
 We are seeking a passionate and experienced Chef to lead our culinary team in a dynamic hospital kitchen environment. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record in menu development, staff management, and food safety compliance. Responsibilities include overseeing all kitchen operations, managing staffing and payroll, ensuring adherence to specialized dietary needs, and maintaining food quality and presentation standards. 
 
 The Chef will collaborate closely with dietetic technicians and dietitians to create flavorful and nutritious recipes, monitor food and labor costs to optimize budgets, and implement effective training programs for kitchen staff. Exceptional communication skills and a commitment to customer service are essential, as well as the ability to resolve guest concerns promptly. Join us to enhance our culinary offerings while fostering a collaborative and productive kitchen atmosphere.

job_description:
Finance and Business Consultant
 
 
 
 We are seeking a motivated and adaptable Finance and Business Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their strong background in accounting and finance to provide expert consultancy in business and property sectors. Key responsibilities include analyzing budgets and financial reports, forecasting project costs, and collaborating with management to develop expense plans. The consultant will also be responsible for identifying cost-saving opportunities and implementing strategies to optimize financial performance. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential, as the role involves working closely with clients and stakeholders. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and critical thinking skills are required. Multilingual abilities, particularly in English and Indonesian, will be an advantage. If you are a self-motivated professional eager to drive business success, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
Finance and Business Consultant
 
 
 
 We are seeking a motivated and adaptable Finance and Business Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their strong background in accounting and finance to provide expert consultancy in business and property sectors. Key responsibilities include analyzing budgets and financial reports, forecasting project costs, and collaborating with management to develop expense plans. The consultant will also be responsible for identifying cost-saving opportunities and implementing strategies to optimize financial performance. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential, as the role involves working closely with clients and stakeholders. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and critical thinking skills are required. Multilingual abilities, particularly in English and Indonesian, will be an advantage. If you are a self-motivated professional eager to drive business success, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
Finance and Business Consultant
 
 
 
 We are seeking a motivated and adaptable Finance and Business Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their strong background in accounting and finance to provide expert consultancy in business and property sectors. Key responsibilities include analyzing budgets and financial reports, forecasting project costs, and collaborating with management to develop expense plans. The consultant will also be responsible for identifying cost-saving opportunities and implementing strategies to optimize financial performance. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential, as the role involves working closely with clients and stakeholders. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and critical thinking skills are required. Multilingual abilities, particularly in English and Indonesian, will be an advantage. If you are a self-motivated professional eager to drive business success, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
Finance and Business Consultant
 
 
 
 We are seeking a motivated and adaptable Finance and Business Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will leverage their strong background in accounting and finance to provide expert consultancy in business and property sectors. Key responsibilities include analyzing budgets and financial reports, forecasting project costs, and collaborating with management to develop expense plans. The consultant will also be responsible for identifying cost-saving opportunities and implementing strategies to optimize financial performance. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential, as the role involves working closely with clients and stakeholders. Proficiency in Microsoft Office and critical thinking skills are required. Multilingual abilities, particularly in English and Indonesian, will be an advantage. If you are a self-motivated professional eager to drive business success, we encourage you to apply.

job_description:
Finance and Leadership Development Specialist
 
 Location: [City, State]
 
 We are seeking a motivated Finance and Leadership Development Specialist to enhance employee morale and productivity within our organization. The ideal candidate will leverage their expertise in finance, project management, and training to support strategic initiatives. Responsibilities include advising management on program-specific matters, developing risk-reduction metrics, and facilitating employee training activities. The specialist will also serve as a liaison between management and staff, addressing inquiries and resolving work-related issues.
 
 Key qualifications include exceptional interpersonal skills, proficiency in data analysis, and a commitment to employee relations. Experience in public speaking and budget planning is essential. A doctoral degree in Organizational Leadership or a related field is preferred. Join us in fostering a positive organizational culture and driving impactful development programs.

job_description:
Finance Manager
 
 
 
 We are seeking a dynamic Finance Manager to lead our financial operations and ensure compliance with GAAP guidelines. The ideal candidate will possess strong analytical skills and a CPA designation, with a proven track record in financial reporting, budgeting, and forecasting. Responsibilities include facilitating monthly financial reporting, preparing GAAP financial statements, and developing financial models for variance analysis. You will collaborate with auditors, oversee contract negotiations, and implement process improvements to enhance operational efficiency. The Finance Manager will also mentor a team, manage internal controls, and contribute to strategic planning initiatives. Strong communication and resourcefulness are essential in fostering partnerships based on accountability and transparency. Join our team to make a significant impact on our financial health and operational success.

job_description:
Finance Consultant
 
 
 
 We are seeking a strategic and analytical Finance Consultant with over 10 years of experience in financial planning, reporting, and analytics. The ideal candidate will prepare monthly payment reports and analytics dashboards for senior management, utilizing Teradata SQL and Oracle Business Intelligence for ad hoc reporting. Proficiency in data analysis through Access databases and Excel is essential. The consultant will support M&A initiatives, negotiate with credit card companies, and assist in new product launches. Experience in managing financial processes and developing business cases is required. The role also involves participating in audits and ensuring compliance with Sarbanes-Oxley regulations. Strong communication skills and a proven ability to provide insights for decision-making are critical. Join our team to drive financial strategies and enhance operational efficiency.

 If you are a results-oriented leader with a passion for financial excellence, we invite you to join our team.

 If you are a results-oriented leader with a passion for financial excellence, we invite you to join our team.

job_description:
Finance Director
 
 Location: [City, State]
 
 We are seeking a motivated Finance Director with a strong background in strategic planning, budgeting, and accounting. The ideal candidate will implement and enhance accounting procedures, specifically using QuickBooks, and manage payroll processing in collaboration with ADP. Proficiency in Microsoft Excel is essential for creating financial worksheets and monthly payroll statements.
 
 Key responsibilities include reviewing financial statements, leading process improvements, and working closely with senior management, including the HR Director and CEO. The successful candidate will also demonstrate leadership in staff development and contribute to compliance and auditing processes.
 
 Qualifications include a Bachelor's degree in Business Administration and experience in financial analysis, Medicaid claims processing, and internal audits. Join our team and drive financial excellence in our organization!

job_description:
Finance Officer
 
 We are seeking a detail-oriented Finance Officer with a strong accounting background and expertise in database management. The ideal candidate will develop and implement internal control policies for budget administration, cash management, and accounting processes. You will coordinate financial planning, oversee budgeting and procurement activities, and maintain compliance with organizational and regulatory standards. 
 
 Responsibilities include preparing financial statements, analyzing operational data for improvement opportunities, and advising management on financial objectives. The Finance Officer will supervise financial reporting tasks, manage payroll functions, and ensure accurate reconciliation of accounts. 
 
 The successful applicant will possess exceptional analytical skills, effective time management abilities, and a collaborative spirit. A Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Accounting or Finance is required, along with a proven track record of achieving cost reductions and enhancing financial efficiency. Join our team to drive financial excellence and support our organizational goals.

job_description:
Engineering Technician
 
 Location: [City, State]
 
 Job Summary:
 We are seeking an experienced Engineering Technician to join our team. The ideal candidate will analyze documentation for production accuracy, create and manage training certifications, and conduct safety audits to ensure a secure work environment. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, especially Excel and PowerPoint, is essential for generating reports and presentations. You will be the primary point of contact for various stakeholders, resolving production issues, managing material transactions using Oracle, and coordinating inspections of discrepant materials. Additionally, you will facilitate weekly MRB meetings and support recycling efforts for materials. A strong understanding of production processes and excellent communication skills are required.
 
 Key Responsibilities:
 - Analyze production documentation and resolve issues.
 - Create training matrices and conduct safety audits.
 - Track material transactions and coordinate with suppliers.
 - Manage DMR/RTS material and support recycling initiatives. 
 
 Qualifications:
 - Strong organizational and analytical skills.
 - Proficient in Microsoft Office and Oracle.

 We are seeking an experienced Engineering Manager with over 25 years of proven expertise in project management, process improvement, and equipment maintenance. The ideal candidate will oversee the installation, testing, and operation of equipment while ensuring compliance with safety and health regulations. Responsibilities include training staff on standard operating procedures, managing multiple projects within budget, and collaborating with various departments to enhance operational efficiency. job_description:
Engineering Technician
 
 We are seeking a skilled Engineering Technician to join our civil engineering team. The ideal candidate will have experience in design and drafting of capital improvement projects, including roadway and utility reconstruction. Responsibilities include creating accurate plans using Microstation, AutoCAD, and GeoPak, conducting TOPO graphic and construction surveys, and performing stormwater assessments to determine impervious area fees. The role also involves maintaining base map drawings and ensuring compliance with project specifications during inspections. Proficiency in surveying equipment such as Trimble GPS and Topcon Total Station is essential. The successful candidate will possess strong problem-solving skills and a commitment to quality in engineering practices. A degree in Civil Engineering Technology or Construction Management is preferred. Join us to contribute to impactful community projects while furthering your expertise in the field.

job_description:
Test Engineer
 
 
 
 We are seeking a skilled Test Engineer with over 10 years of experience in electronics manufacturing and test engineering. The ideal candidate will be responsible for debugging complex electronic products, conducting reliability testing, and performing root cause analysis on hardware components. Proficiency in using test equipment such as oscilloscopes and network analyzers is essential, along with experience in Python scripting for test automation.

The candidate should possess excellent problem-solving skills and be proactive in contributing to continuous improvement initiatives within the organization. 
 
 Join us to leverage your expertise and drive innovation in a dynamic technology environment.

job_description:
Engineering Assistant
 
 We are seeking a motivated Engineering Assistant to support our product and process engineering team. The ideal candidate will have experience in new product development and process improvement, particularly within the automotive sector. Responsibilities include developing and implementing manufacturing metrics to enhance safety, quality, and cost efficiency, as well as conducting root cause analysis and PFMEA. Developed APQP, cost estimations and integrated new fuel injectors models in the remanufacturing process line.  Performed PFMEA, root cause analysis and lead cross functional teams to resolve quality downtime issues.  Sustained and monitored lean manufacturing (5S, workplace safety, Kaizen, Single piece flow) and drove continuous improvement.         06/2013   to   06/2016     Engineer    Company Name   －   City  ,   State      Designed, developed, tested and introduced new product in the manufacturing line.  Developed control plans and schedules to support prototype development, pre production and zero defect production parts launc h.  Studied market forecast, conducted benchmarking and manufacturing cost analysis for new product introduction.  Lead APQP, DVP&R and PPAP development and conducted DFMEA for new product development.  Scheduled and coordinated phases of project (cost, tooling, equipment,) to develop 'World class model line manufacturing' imp lementing (TPS).  Successfully launched new product assembly project worth $100 million adhering to Toyota standards.  Performed design reviews, documented BOM and created assembly process documentations.  Reduced manufacturing costs by 30% by improving SQD (Safety, Quality & Delivery) KPI's metrics.  Performed and ensured quality and reliability of processes and developed validation recovery plans.  Spearheaded cost estimations and closure of non-conformance reports using quality tools (Pareto charts, Fishbone analysis, 8D, 5Why, FMEA).  Developed actions for IPQPR's (In process quality problem reports), SQPR's (Supplier quality problem reports) to present to Japanese quality teams.  Prepared product and process engineering change requests (ECR's) documentations, cost reduction proposals and presented to management.  Developed manufacturing process layout, control plans, work instructions and PFMEA.  Major Projects.  University of Michigan Dearborn Product Development - Designed a manually operated juicer using CATIA V5, prototyped the part using additive manufacturing (3D Printing), used benchmarking, customer surveys, DFMEA and brainstorming methodologies to build its business portfolio using lean canvas.  Occupant package design - Assessing driver requirements like seat track length, head clearance, entrance height, steering wheel height and diameter, accelerator heal point and other important driver's requirement to design a new compact sedan with the help of Anthropometric data and SAEJ1100v005, SAEJ1516v002, SAEJ1517v002 and benchmarking analysis.  Vehicle package analysis and evaluation of cargo compartment - Analyzed vehicle attribute requirements like cost, quality, operation and packaging of cargo compartment by benchmarking three entry level sedans and evaluating the results using ANOVA for customer feedback reliability.  Analysis of driver door interior trim panel using Quality function deployment (QFD) - Evaluated HMI logical layout and packaging of systems in interior trim panel by benchmarking compact sedans, interviewed customers for user experience, used QFD to take suggestions to find area of improvements.  Exterior and mechanical package analysis - Developed interface diagram and interface matrix to represent various functions between components.  Studied vehicle anatomy by decomposing the vehicle into systems, sub-systems, and components.  Vehicle body side aperture spot welding - Conducted detailed analysis of spot welding of BIW, determined robot base and end effector motion and the factors for complete station design using 4M.  Gearbox FMEA - Conducted detailed study on potential failure causes in 6X4 truck gearbox casing failure in fracture using DFMEA and PFMEA.  Implemented DFA and DFM to derive optimal design for ease of assembly and disassembly of gearbox casing.  Design for assembly - Proposed assembly line for plant with 138 stations for volume requirement of 240k vehicles, analyzed the JPH, throughput, bottleneck, labor hours, number of shifts and operators, length of station and line speed.  Six Sigma - Implemented lean six sigma concepts to improve the efficiency of base coat usage at body paint shop by DMAIC methodology. job_description:
Engineering Technician
 
 We are seeking an experienced Engineering Technician to join our dynamic team in the Electronic Technology field. The ideal candidate will possess extensive knowledge in testing and analyzing complex circuit packs and systems, with a strong background in fiber optics since 1999. You will be responsible for managing production activities, ensuring 100% on-time delivery, and collaborating with R&D teams on experimental projects. 
 
 Key responsibilities include troubleshooting at the component level, interpreting manufacturing documentation, and executing quality control measures. The ability to work independently as well as part of a team is essential. Strong critical thinking, effective multitasking, and excellent problem-solving skills are a must. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and schematics reading is required. 
 
 Join us to leverage your skills in a challenging and rewarding environment where your contributions will directly impact production efficiency and quality.
